  "body": "This commit adds a generic client-server implementation based in part on Erlang's [gen_server](http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/gen_server.html) module. Here is an example of an implementation of how one could implement the cell example described in _Concurrent Programming in ML_ (Reppy, 1999, pp. 42-45):\n\n``` rust\nuse extra::comm::server::*;\n\nstruct Server { value: int }\n\nstruct Get;\nstruct Put(int);\n\nimpl GenericServer<int, (), Get, Put, int, ()> for Server {\n    fn init(x: int) -> Result<Server, ()> {\n        Ok(Server { value: x })\n    }\n\n    fn handle_call(&mut self, _: Get) -> Reply<int, ()> {\n        Reply(self.value)\n    }\n\n    fn handle_cast(&mut self, Put(x): Put) -> Reply<Continue, ()> {\n        self.value = x; Reply(Continue)\n    }\n}\n\nstruct Cell {\n    priv client: SharedClient<Get, Put, int>,\n}\n\nimpl Cell {\n    fn new(x: int) -> Cell {\n        Cell { client: spawn_server::<int, (), Get, Put, int, (), Server>(x)\n                .unwrap().into_shared() }\n    }\n\n    fn get(&self) -> int { self.client.call(Get) }\n    fn put(&self, x: int) { self.client.cast(Put(x)) }\n}\n\nimpl Clone for Cell {\n    fn clone(&self) -> Cell {\n        Cell { client: self.client.clone() }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAnd here is an example of the storage cell in use:\n\n``` rust\nlet cell = Cell::new(1);\nassert_eq!(cell.get(), 1);\ncell.put(2);\nassert_eq!(cell.get(), 2);\nassert_eq!(cell.get(), 2);\n\nlet cell2 = cell.clone();\nassert_eq!(cell.get(), 2);\ncell2.put(3);\nassert_eq!(cell.get(), 3);\nassert_eq!(cell2.get(), 3);\n```\n",
